      "content": "For maximum control, the goal is always neatness, regardless of natural texture. For those with thicker or curlier hair, a very tight, well-maintained cut that is kept short on the sides and neatly shaped on top is key; it shows discipline. Straight hair should be slicked back or neatly side-parted, never messy. The key takeaway is that the hair should look intentional, not like it was just allowed to grow.",
